definition.value: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol with myristoyl and palmitoleoyl as 1- and 2-acyl groups respectively.
A prephenic acid having (1s,4s)-cis-configuration.
A 2-hydroxy fatty acid anion with a chain that is composed of 26 carbons and 1 double bond (position unspecified).
A 2-hydroxy fatty acid anion with a chain that is composed of 26 carbons and 2 double bond (positions unspecified).
A very long-chain fatty acid anion with a chain that is composed of 26 carbons and 2 double bond (positions unspecified).
A polyunsaturated fatty acid anion composed of 24 carbons with 2 double bonds in unknown positions.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol that has myristoyl and linoleoyl as 1- and 2-acyl groups respectively.
A 2-hydroxy fatty acid anion with a chain that is composed of 24 carbons and 2 double bond (positions unspecified).
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol that has palmitoyl and palmitoleoyl as 1- and 2-acyl groups respectively.
A linear dextrin or short chained amylose (DP 20-30) that can be produced by enzymatic hydrolysis of the alpha-1,6 glycosidic bonds or debranching amylopectin.
Any cyclodepsipeptide that is a derivative of a chondramide.
A cardiolipin in which all four phosphatidyl acyl groups are specified as linoleoyl.
A cardiolipin in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1, 1' and 2 are specified as linoleoyl, while that at position 2' is specified as oleoyl.
A cardiolipin in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1, 1' and 2 are specified as linoleoyl, while that at position 2' is specified as palmitoyl.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as palmitoyl and (11Z,14Z)-eicosadienoyl respectively.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as palmitoyl and (8Z,11Z,14Z-eicosatrienoyl respectively.

A phytoceramide is a ceramide where the sphingoid base is hydroxylated at position 4. These backbone bases can be 14 to 20 carbons long, either straight chain or branched. The N-linked fatty acids are typically saturated or monounsaturated with chain lengths from 14 to 26 carbon atoms; the presence of a hydroxyl group on carbon 2 is fairly common. In the illustrated generalised structure, R1 = OH, OX (where X = acyl, glycosyl, phosphate, phosphonate, etc.), or H.
An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of any ceramide 1-phosphate.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as palmitoyl and (7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z)-docosatetraenoyl  respectively.

Any of the lignans with a 9-aryl-1-oxo-1,3-dihydronaphtho[2,3-c]furan-4-yl glycoside skeleton originally isolated from Cleistanthus collinus, a toxic deciduous shrub. While all parts of the plant are poisonous, the leaves in particular are used as a suicide poison by young women in rural parts of southern India. Cleistanthins A and B have been particularly associated with the toxicity of the plant, with cleistanthin A being more potent than cleistanthin B.
A member of the class of cleistanthins that is cleistanthin A in which the 3,4-di-O-methyl-D-xylopyranosyl group is replaced by a beta-D-glucopyranosyl group.

A member of the class of cleistanthins that is cleistanthin A in which the hydroxy group at position 4 of the glucoside moiety has been converted to the corresponding 2,3-di-O-methyl-beta-D-xylopyranoside.
A member of the class of cleistanthins that is cleistanthin A in which the 3,4-di-O-methyl-D-xylopyranosyl group is replaced by a 2,3,4-tri-O-methyl-D-xylofuranosyl group.
A cationic sphingoid obtained by protonation of the amino group of any 2-amino-1,3-dihydroxysphingoid base.
A cationic sphingoid obtained by protonation of the amino group of any 3-dehydrosphingoid base. Major species at pH 7.3.
A fatty acyl-AMP that results from the formal condensation of the phosphoryl group of AMP with the carboxyl group of tetradecanoic (myristic) acid.
Any glycoside that is a derivative of a cleistanthin.
A fatty acyl-AMP that results from the formal condensation of the phosphoryl group of AMP with the carboxyl group of hexadecanoic (palmitic) acid.
An amino sulfonic acid that is taurine substituted by an acetyl group at the N atom.

A member of the class of cleistanthins that is cleistanthin C in which the hydroxy group at position 4 of the 2,3-di-O-methyl-beta-D-xylopyranosyl moiety has been converted to the corresponding 2,3,5-tri-O-methyl-D-xylofuranoside.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as palmitoleoyl.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as palmitoleoyl and stearoyl respectively.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as palmitoleoyl and linoleoyl respectively.
A polyprenylhydroquinone having the structure of a ubiquinol with hydroxy replacing methoxy at C-5.
A 3-demethylubiquinol in which the polyprenyl chain contains 9 prenyl units.
A ubiquinol in which the polyprenyl substituent is nonaprenyl.
A FAHFA (fatty acid ester of a hydroxy fatty acid) obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of palmitic acid with the hydroxy group of 9-hydroxyoctadecanoic acid (9-hydroxystearic acid).
A fatty acid ester obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of any fatty acid with the hydroxy group of any hydroxy fatty acid.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate(2-) in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at postions 1 and 2 are specified as heptadecanoyl and lauroyl respectively.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate(2-) in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at postions 1 and 2 are specified as heptadecanoyl and myristoyl respectively.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate(2-) in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at postions 1 and 2 are specified as heptadecanoyl and stearoyl respectively.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate(2-) in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at postions 1 and 2 are specified as heptadecanoyl and palmitoyl respectively.
A 3-demethylubiquinol in which the polyprenyl chain contains 7 prenyl units.
A ubiquinol in which the polyprenyl substituent is heptaprenyl.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as stearoyl and 8Z,11Z,14Z-icosa-8,11,14-trienoyl respectively.
An RNA fragment comprised of two guanosine, one adenosine, one uridine and four cytidine residues connected by 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages in the sequence G-A-C-C-C-C-U-G.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as stearoyl and 7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z-docosatetraenoyl respectively.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as oleoyl and gondoyl respectively.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as oleoyl and 8Z,11Z,14Z-eicosatrienoyl respectively.
